CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775596265
OL,3,CKnife crime 'hotspots' to be earmarked
OL,4,Cfor surge in policing
OL,6,FThe vast majority of knife crime
OL,7,Fincidents happen in the same locations
OL,8,Frepeatedly, according to the Home
OL,9,FOffice.
OL,11,FThe mapping technology, which is
OL,12,Faccurate to 0.1 square kilometres,
OL,13,Fwill allow forces to send extra
OL,14,Fresources such as police patrols,
OL,15,FCCTV, knife arches and Live Facial
OL,16,FRecognition to the worst affected
OL,17,Fareas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
